Hard rules (orchestrator-house, derived from canon — surfaced so you don't miss them):
- **`class="scene clip"` on the scene div** — `clip` is required by HF lint on any element with `data-start`/`data-duration` (the runtime keys hard-cut visibility off `.clip`). Standalone-composition canon (`transitions/catalog.md` L13) omits both timing attrs *and* the `clip` class on scene divs because root timing covers them; our orchestrator-house Pattern A keeps timing on each scene for the v4 visibility shim, so `clip` MUST come along.
- **CSS scoping** — every rule prefixed with `#scene-{{ scene_id }}`. No bare class selectors. Inlining is collision-prone otherwise.
- **`tl.fromTo()` only** for entrances — never `tl.from()`, never bare `gsap.from()`. Non-linear seek breaks otherwise.
- **No `data-composition-id` on the scene div** — that attribute belongs to the root composition only (Pattern A; see catalog.md L13).
- **No `<template>` wrapper.** Pattern B (sub-compositions) is broken upstream; this fragment is inlined as-is.
- **No `<script src=".../gsap...">`** — root scaffold supplies GSAP once.
- **Density floor**: ≥ 8 elements visible at the hero frame, ≥ 2 BG decoratives with ambient motion (`tl.to()` on the seekable `tl`, never bare `gsap.to()`).
- **≥ 3 distinct eases** (Animation Guardrails); first entrance offset 0.1–0.3s.
- **Final-fade (HR 4)**: permitted iff `is_final == True`. Otherwise NO `tl.to(..., {opacity: 0})` on the scene container — scene-to-scene transitions are root-scope and authored elsewhere.
- **Avoid the literal substring `repeat:` followed by ` -1`** — even in JS comments — HF lint regex false-positive. Use `repeat: 999` or omit.
- **opacity initial state**: `0` for non-first scenes (the future transitions node fades them in). First scene starts visible.

